{"id":"nora-d2p","title":"Optimize commands for AI-agent usage","description":"Make nora's one-shot commands (add, import, tags add --ai, fix, etc.) work well when called by AI agents like Claude Code. This means: clean machine-readable output (JSON mode or structured text), non-interactive fallbacks (skip fzf prompts when stdin isn't a TTY), clear exit codes, and potentially a --json flag for structured output. The goal is that an AI agent can shell out to nora commands as tools — e.g. claude-code could run 'nora add' to format and save a note, 'nora search' to find notes, 'nora tags' to manage taxonomy, all without human interaction.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-12T17:53:53.600345950Z","created_by":"anna","updated_at":"2026-03-12T17:53:53.600345950Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
